    "summary": "wind 28-33 kt · 998 mb · High",
    "started_at": "2026-04-04T11:30:00+00:00",
    "updated_at": "2026-04-04T11:30:00+00:00",
    "location_text": "12.7S 171.2E",
    "lat": -12.7,
    "lon": 171.2,
    "source_primary": "JTWC-ABPW",
    "source_secondary": "disturbance",
    "status": "high",
    "map_url": "https://www.google.com/maps?q=-12.7,171.2",
    "official_link": "https://www.google.com/maps?q=-12.7,171.2",
    "country_code": null,
    "payload": {
      "item_type": "disturbance",
      "source": "jtwc_abpw",
      "source_key": "jtwc_abpw|south_pacific_area|invest_91p",
      "content_hash": "bf9d294bf34c3231",
      "platform_summary": "12.7S 171.2E | winds 28-33 kt | 998 mb | HIGH",
      "platform_location": "12.7S 171.2E",
      "wind": "28-33 kt",
      "risk_48h": null,
      "risk_7d": null,
      "next_update": null,
      "raw_text": "(1) THE AREA OF CONVECTION (INVEST 91P) PREVIOUSLY LOCATED NEAR \n12.3S 171.3E IS NOW LOCATED NEAR 12.7S 171.2E, APPROXIMATELY 345 NM \nNORTH-NORTHEAST OF PORT VILA. MULTISPECTRAL SATELLITE IMAGERY (MSI) \nREVEALS A BROAD LOW LEVEL CIRCULATION CENTER (LLCC) WITH AN ELONGATED \nBUT SLOWLY CONSOLIDATING CENTER AND RECENTLY DEVELOPING DEEP \nCONVECTION ALONG THE EASTERN SIDE OF THE CIRCULATION. A 040959Z ASCAT \nPASS SHOWS A DEFINED CIRCULATION WITH STRONGER WINDS OF 25-30 KNOTS \nWRAPPING AROUND THE SOUTH AND EASTERN SIDE OF THE CIRCULATION, WITH A \nFEW ISOLATED PATCHES OF 35 KNOTS EMBEDDED UNDER THE DEEPEST CONVECTIVE \nCELLS. ENVIRONMENTAL ANALYSIS REVEALS FAVORABLE CONDITIONS FOR \nDEVELOPMENT WITH LOW TO MODERATE VERTICAL WIND SHEAR (15-20 KNOTS), \nGOOD DIFFLUENT OUTFLOW ALOFT, AND WARM SEA SURFACE TEMPERATURES (29-30 \nC). GLOBAL MODELS ARE IN FAIR AGREEMENT THAT INVEST 91P WILL CONTINUE \nTO HAVE STEADY DEVELOPMENT AND A SOUTHWARD TRACK OVER THE NEXT 12 TO \n24 HOURS. MAXIMUM SUSTAINED SURFACE WINDS ARE ESTIMATED AT 28 TO 33 \nKNOTS. MINIMUM SEA LEVEL PRESSURE IS ESTIMATED TO BE NEAR 998 MB. THE \nPOTENTIAL FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF A SIGNIFICANT TROPICAL CYCLONE WITHIN \nTHE NEXT 24 HOURS IS UPGRADED TO HIGH. SEE REF B (WTPS21 PGTW 041130) \nFOR FURTHER DETAILS.",
      "metadata": {
        "basin_section": "SOUTH PACIFIC AREA (WEST COAST OF SOUTH AMERICA TO 135 EAST)",
        "invest_id": "91P",
        "lat": -12.7,
        "lon": 171.2,
        "wind_kt_min": 28,
        "wind_kt_max": 33,
        "pressure_mb": 998,
        "development_phrase": "UPGRADED TO",
        "development_level": "HIGH",
        "bulletin_issue_at": "2026-04-04T11:30:00+00:00"
      }
    },
